}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{The course is designed to develop students' understanding of consumers 
and their behaviour, which is a key prerequisite to the development 
of an adequate marketing programme\'2e }\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{\~}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{{\b
Learning outcomes and competences: }}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{Upon successful completion of this course, students will be able to:\line
\line
\_ Explain the central role of the consumer in the market offerings 
of companies and other organizations;\line
\_ Apply theories and models of consumer behavior within the formulation 
of a company's marketing strategies;\line
\_ Identify what information about consumers needs to be gathered 
for marketing purposes;\line
\_ Characterize the different types of values offered by companies 
to the end customer and to society as a whole\'2e}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{\~}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{{\b
Course contents: }}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{The course introduces the main determinants of consumer behaviour, 
covering the buying decision process and its key psychological, social, 
and cultural influences\'2e\line
Students will complete two group projects applying course concepts 
in practice\'2e In the first, groups select a brand and analyse it 
throughout the semester, culminating in an original advertisement 
that demonstrates a chosen consumer behaviour concept\'2e In the second, 
students carry out a consumer behaviour experiment and present their 
findings in a short video\'2e\line
The students will be required to participate actively in the lectures, 
discussing their results\'2e \line
\line
The course is focused in particular on the following areas: \line
\_ Definition of consumer behaviour it today's world and its importance 
for marketing\line
\_ Buying behaviour and consumer decision making\line
\line
Psychological factors in consumer behaviour:\line
\_ Perception of the outside world, perception of the self\line
\_ Motivation, values\line
\_ Learning, memory\line
\line
Social factors in consumer behaviour:\line
\_ Reference groups and consumer behaviour\line
\_ Economic factors and consumer behaviour\line
\line
\_ Culture and consumer behaviour\line
\_ Consumer culture, transformations in consumer culture, their importance 
for marketing and the role of marketing in consumer culture }\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
